---
import { legalDocuments } from "../../../site.config.mjs";

interface Props {
  supportHref: string;
}

const { supportHref } = Astro.props as Props;
---

<h1>PlanKept Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>
  <strong>Effective Date:</strong> {legalDocuments.privacy.effectiveDate}<br />
  <strong>Version:</strong> {legalDocuments.privacy.version}
</p>

<p>
  This Privacy Policy explains how PlanKept processes personal information when you use the
  PlanKept pages on this site, including the public app page under <code>/apps/PlanKept/</code>,
  the support and legal pages under <code>/PlanKept/</code>, the wish-list flow, and any future
  app experience that links to this policy.
</p>

<p>
  PlanKept is currently in an early public stage. Its page on this personal site is live now as
  the public support, legal, and interest-signup surface.
</p>

<p>Contact:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Email: <code>alekgameshelp2@gmail.com</code></li>
  <li>Support page: <code>{supportHref}</code></li>
</ul>

<h2>Summary</h2>

<ul>
  <li>The current website is intentionally lightweight.</li>
  <li>We may receive the information you choose to send through support email or wish-list email.</li>
  <li>
    The core in-app PlanKept flow is intended to stay on device by default, including plan text,
    proof-review content, submitted photos, and AI conversations used inside the app.
  </li>
  <li>
    If you click through to an external wish-list form or external email service, that third party
    may also process your information under its own terms and privacy policy.
  </li>
  <li>We do not sell your personal data.</li>
  <li>
    If the future app introduces additional data processing, this policy should be updated before
    or with that change.
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

<p>We may collect or receive:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Your email address if you contact support or join the wish list by email</li>
  <li>Your name or nickname if you choose to include it</li>
  <li>The message or notes you send us</li>
  <li>
    Basic technical request information normally involved in website delivery, such as IP address,
    browser type, and request timing
  </li>
</ul>

<p>
  If a future PlanKept app links to this policy, additional categories may be added here before
  those features are launched or materially changed.
</p>

<p>
  The intended local-first design for the core app flow means plan text, proof-review content such
  as photos or written explanations, and AI conversations used inside the app may be processed on
  device without being sent to us by default. If remote purchase, account, sync, or similar
  service-backed features are introduced later, this policy should be updated before or with that
  change.
</p>

<h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>

<p>We may use information to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>respond to support requests</li>
  <li>keep track of early interest in the product</li>
  <li>improve the website and launch flow</li>
  <li>protect the service and investigate misuse</li>
  <li>comply with legal obligations</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Legal Bases</h2>

<p>Where applicable, we rely on one or more of these grounds:</p>

<ul>
  <li>your consent, where you choose to contact us or submit information</li>
  <li>performance of a requested service, such as responding to support</li>
  <li>legitimate interests, such as maintaining and improving the website</li>
  <li>compliance with legal obligations</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Sharing</h2>

<p>
  We may share information with service providers that help operate the site or communications
  flow, such as:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>website hosting providers</li>
  <li>email providers</li>
  <li>any external wish-list form or list service you intentionally use</li>
</ul>

<p>
  We may also disclose information if required by law or if reasonably necessary to protect
  rights, safety, or the service.
</p>

<h2>5. Retention</h2>

<p>
  We keep personal information only as long as reasonably necessary for support, wish-list
  management, legal compliance, or legitimate business operations.
</p>

<p>
  Because PlanKept is still early, retention practices may be simplified for now. If retention
  becomes more complex later, this policy should be updated.
</p>

<h2>6. Data Security</h2>

<p>
  We use reasonable measures intended to protect information, but no method of storage or
  transmission is perfectly secure.
</p>

<h2>7. International Transfers</h2>

<p>
  If our service providers process information in other countries, your information may be
  transferred internationally and handled according to the provider&apos;s safeguards and legal
  requirements.
</p>

<h2>8. Children&apos;s Privacy</h2>

<p>
  PlanKept is not intended for children under 16, and we do not knowingly seek to collect personal
  information from children under 16.
</p>

<h2>9. Your Rights</h2>

<p>
  Depending on where you live, you may have rights to request access, correction, deletion, or
  restriction of some personal information.
</p>

<p>To make a request, email <code>alekgameshelp2@gmail.com</code>.</p>

<h2>10. Third-Party Links</h2>

<p>
  The website may link to third-party websites, including external wish-list pages and Apple&apos;s
  standard App Store terms. Those sites are governed by their own policies and terms.
</p>

<h2>11. Changes To This Policy</h2>

<p>
  We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the effective date and
  version above.
</p>

<h2>12. Contact</h2>

<p>For privacy questions, contact:</p>

<ul>
  <li><code>alekgameshelp2@gmail.com</code></li>
</ul>
